OL,3,CWorst delivery firms revealed as
OL,4,Cparcel problems reach record high
OL,6,FThe most common issue reported by
OL,7,Fcustomers was the courier leaving
OL,8,Fbefore they had time to get to the
OL,9,Fdoor, with 29% affected.
OL,11,FThe research found 24% of people
OL,12,Freported packages being left in
OL,13,Finsecure locations, with 24% also
OL,14,Fexperiencing parcels arriving late.
OL,16,FCitizens Advice said its findings
OL,17,Fshowed there had been "marginal"
OL,18,Fchanges in scores over the last five
OL,19,Fyears, but the overall picture was one
OL,20,Fof consumers being "persistently
OL,21,Ffailed" by parcel companies.
